div.div:
Beats are deployed on all the instances to monitor, including the instance running the ELK stack. Beats ship data to the ELK stack, either directly to Elasticsearch or via Logstash when data preprocessing is required.
Official and community Beats are used to collect specific information periodically about the hosts and Docker containers. For example, Filebeat ships logs while Metricbeat is used to collect metrics from the systems and services, including CPU, memory, filesystem and network usage.
